  "final_answer": "Based on the provided graph evidence, some potential drug alternatives to Heena are:\n* Dihydroergotamine Mesylate Drops, which contains the identical chemical compound Ethanol, found in Heena.\n* Alkeran (melphalan), which also contains the identical chemical compound Ethanol.\n* Vincristine Sulfate Injection (Alternative), containing the identical chemical compound Ethanol.\n* Sulfamoxole + Trimethoprim Veterinary Injectable Solution (400 mg + 80 mg/10 mL), with the identical chemical compound Ethanol.\nNote that Ebselen Liposomal Injection, mentioned in the draft, contains Methanol, which is also found in Heena, but the relation is identical, so it can be considered.\n\nPlease note that the dosage information for these alternatives is not available, and it's essential to consult a healthcare professional before using any medication. Remember, it's crucial to consult a healthcare professional before making any decisions about your health or medication, as they can provide personalized advice and help you make informed decisions.",
